<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,786,1644,1860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[174,230,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Notes</emphasis>
. – This liverwort is characteristic of the 
<collectingRegion box="[662,734,1644,1668]" country="Colombia" name="Choco" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Chocó</collectingRegion>
biogeographic region of 
<collectingCountry box="[359,465,1676,1700]" name="Colombia" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[517,606,1676,1700]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and additionally occurs in the eastern foothills of the northern Andes (SHI &amp; ZHU, 2005). Allioni collected this subspecies twice along the Río Sapotillo; one collection was described by Stephani as a new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.W.Evans" authorityYear="1907" box="[301,442,1804,1828]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Leucolejeunea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[301,442,1804,1828]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Leucolejeunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the other one as a new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[164,289,1836,1860]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Marchesinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,289,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Marchesinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
